Paper summary\
-------------\
The paper describes an electricity market model based on an open agent based simulation framework.\
\
Comments for author\
-------------------\
Dear authors, \
thank you for your paper. I have following remarks, which should be taken into account:\
\
- You develop a "further" ABM for electricity markets. There are plenty of ABMs for electricity markets and also other modelling approaches (e.g. optimisation, etc.). It is unclear, what is the overall benefit to develop a new one (except for beeing open, which is also the case for some other models). Why using an ABM instead of a clear mathematical formulation (e.g. optimisation approach)?\
\
- You write: "Stochasticity includes varying fuel prices throughout a year, and varying VC and WACC." What exactly does this mean? How did you model this? Is is a two-stage stochastic programming? Or is it just a Monte-Carlo simulation. Please be more precise. \
\
- You write: "We are unable to model short-term storage dueto ElecSIM taking yearly time-steps." What does this mean? How many time steps do you model per year. Only 1. Does this make any sense?\
\
- You just show the model, but no case study. THe scenario testing (and it's figures) are completly not clear and not well described. What can we see on the figues? What can we learn from it?\
\
