Paper summary\
-------------\
The paper presents an open-sourced agent-based modeling framework for examining the effects of policy decisions on long-term investment policies in the electricity sector. It is designed for non-experts to rapidly prototype new ideas, and implements a modular framework, which is a little underrepresented in the submitted paper.\
\
Comments for author\
-------------------\
I enjoyed reading the paper and its style of presentation. The motivation is clear and concise and the need for the tool that is being developed (ElecSIM) is well motivated \'96 with a representative overview of the state of the art. \
The technical details are a little underrepresented (the authors state that the tool can be extended by experts with additional modules, but definitely not based on this documentation ;-).\
As such it is a (albeit short) nice contribution to the workshop providing ample opportunity for discussion.}